Transferred from Hampshire to Surrey on 30.9.1895. See also Table 
    2, note (g).

Created 1894 out of the parishes of Farnham and Waverley. Abolished 
    1.4.1933 and divided between the parishes of Tilford and Farnham.

That part which until 1.4.1933 formed the parish of 
    Shottermill. See also Table 2, note (g).

Created 1.4.1933 out of the parishes of Frensham and Elstead. 
    See also Table 2, note (g).

Created 1.10.1896 out of the parish of Frensham. Abolished 1.4.1933 
    and added to the parish of Haslemere. See also Table 2, note (g).

Created 1.4.1933 out of the parishes of Farnham Rural and Elstead. 
    See also Table 2, note (g).
Abolished 1894 and added to the parish of Farnham Rural.
